<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100290539223203></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100290539223203><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=quest.html?quest=695&mid=100290539223203>Focus Items</a> <a id=fs8 href=quest.html?quest=695&mid=100290539223203#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50837><span id= >Ghoumer</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 12th 12:49 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>All the items, except the Broom, Stien, Shovel and Torch, I bought from vendors throught Freeport and Commons. <br><br>The Ruby can be bought from a vendor in the Cleric Guild in North Freeport. I bought mine in auction for 125pp, saving about 6pp.<br><br>The other three gems can be bought in regular jewelery vendors, like the blue building in North Freeport.<br><br>Toes: Third Inn - East Commons, Jade Inn - North Freeport, and various vendors.<br><br>Griffon Feathers: Arcane Acadamey - West Freeport.<br><br>Gargoyle Eye: Arcane Academy and other various vendors.<br><br>Mermaid Scale: Boomba the Big - West Freeport.<br><br>Fire Drake Scale: Forgotten vendor - I believe it was in commons, though, it may have been at the Arcane Academy.<br><br>I finished all four quests at the same time, earlier this week. I find it quite disappointing that the amount of experience gained from this was less then a blue mob would have given me, at 26th level. I can't see any experience given at the "proper" minimum level of 33. Very odd. I don't see why they even give you the "You gained experience" message.<br><br>As far as how much it helps for lower then 34th or whatever level, I don't see a huge difference, if any. I have not done testing as far as log files and such, but, pets summoned with these items are still blue to me, regardless of whether I'm using the item or not. There doesn't seem to be an increase in damage, either. Unless, I'm getting fairly unlucky.....<br><br><br>Good luck to you.<br>Ghoumer &lt;Steel Thunder&gt;<br>The Seventh Hammer<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
