	   <tr><td colspan=2>Shaman get their first charisma boost spell at level 14 and enchanters get their first at level 20, both classes eventually get better versions but these are the lowest levels each class can cast them on you.  Bards also get a charisma boosting song but you must be grouped with them and it is a level 59 song.  It seems that somewhere around 100-110 charisma is the point where vendors give you the best prices with indifferent faction, it's slightly less if they are amiable or better and if they are apprehensive I don't think you can get the best prices from.  Enchanters and bards get faction increasing spells/songs but they only work for the enchanter or the bard.  Some classes/races can also use sneak from behind a merchant to get to indifferent.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
